Former National Football League star O.J.
Simpson was sentenced to 15 years in prison for armed robbery and kidnapping during a 2007 raid in a Los Vegas hotel.
His co-accused Clarence Stewart was also sentenced to 15 years for the same charges.
With tears in his eyes Simpson apologized for his crimes to the judge, he claimed he was just getting back his own stolen items.
Two of the five other defendants testified against Simpson and Stewart.
Lawyers for both said they will appeal the convictions.
